HAWAII'S BIG ISLAND:

The Big Island has 11 of the 13 world climatic regions, making
it the most diverse Hawaiian island and offering something for
everyone...

- visit the orchid gardens and hike through the tropical rain forest
  on the eastern side of the island

- visit historical sites and experience fantastic snorkeling on the
  western side of the island

- relax at the sunny beach resorts on the northern part of the island

- don't miss the Volcano National Park and macadamia nut farms on the
  southern end of the island

- golf at some of the most incredible courses in the world!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Big Island "must sees"

- Waipi'o Valley - once the home of kings of old Hawaii

- Rainbow Falls - one of the Big Island's loveliest waterfalls

- Black Sand Beaches - made up of pulverized lava, located on the
  south-eastern cliff

- White Sand Beaches - Hapuna State Beach Park, Anaehoomalu Beach,
  and Magic Sands Beach, Kailua

- Volcanoes National Park - the number one visitor attraction in the
  state is also home to Kilauea Volcano, the world's most active volcano
  which continues to pour into the ocean - making the Big Island even
  bigger each day!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

Be sure to take advantage of the fantastic tours available:
- Dan McSweeney's Whale Watching
- Island Breeze Lu'au
- Fluming the Ditch (kayak trip)
- Captain Bean's Dinner Cruise
- Deluxe Morning Luncheon Cruise

And don't forget about your Dollar rental car to truly "discover"
the Big Island.

You've been waiting all year long for a sale like this... so book
now before it's too late!

